The paper discusses the expressivity of Markov logic networks (MLNs), which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces complex MLNs, which are a novel extension of standard MLNs, and discusses their properties. This could potentially fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or signal processing (cs.IT) due to the use of Fourier transforms. Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm for computing relational marginal polytopes, which could be relevant to the field of social networks (cs.SI).
